OL,3,CWhat is vitamin B12 and are you
OL,4,Cdeficient?
OL,6,FThe vitamin B12 helps keep the body's
OL,7,Fblood and nerve cells healthy and a
OL,8,Flack of it can cause anaemia.
OL,10,FAround one in 20 people aged 65 to 74
OL,11,Fare thought to be B12 deficient, while
OL,12,Fone in 10 people aged 75 and over are
OL,13,Flacking in the vitamin, according to
OL,14,Fthe .
OL,16,FNew guidance on how doctors diagnose
OL,17,FB12 deficiencies was by The National
OL,18,FInstitute for Health and Care
OL,19,FExcellence (NICE) on Wednesday,
OL,20,Ffollowing issues of under diagnosis
OL,21,Fand people being mistreated.
